notes/Coding/CSS-ideas.content:
Colors
First define your basic colors using OKLCH.
:root {
  /* Raw LCH values: Lightness, Chroma, Hue */
  --lch-blue: 54% 0.15 255;
  --lch-red: 51% 0.2 31;
  --lch-green: 65% 0.23 142;

  /* Semantic colors built on primitives */
  --color-link: oklch(var(--lch-blue));
  --color-negative: oklch(var(--lch-red));
  --color-positive: oklch(var(--lch-green));
}

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --lch-blue: 72% 0.16 248;   /* Lighter, slightly desaturated */
    --lch-red: 74% 0.18 29;
    --lch-green: 75% 0.20 145;
  }
}
Then, you can use native CSS functions like color-mix() to modify these base colors:
.card {
  --card-color: oklch(var(--lch-blue-dark));

  /* Derive an entire color palette from one variable */
  --card-bg: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card-color) 4%, var(--color-canvas));
  --card-text: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card-color) 30%, var(--color-ink));
  --card-border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card-color) 33%, transparent);
}
This feels much more intuitive, and more controlled, than coming up with various hex values and sprinkling them throughout your stylesheets.
Spacing
Use character width for horizontal spacing, and rem for vertical spacing
:root {
  --inline-space: 1ch;      /* Horizontal: one character width */
  --block-space: 1rem;      /* Vertical: one root em */
}

.component {
  padding-inline: var(--inline-space);
  margin-block: var(--block-space);
}
References

Vanilla CSS is all you need
Modern CSS patterns in Campfire

notes/Quartz-customizations/Disable-Fold.content:
Quartz automatically generates index pages for folders, and shows a list of all pages under that folder.
You can create your own index.md file to change the title and add any content you want, but disabling the list of pages was not as easy.
I ended up editing FolderContent.txs directly, to look for an option called hideFolderContent in the page frontmatter.
// check if folder content should be displayed according to frontmatter
const showFolderContent: boolean =
	fileData.frontmatter !== true

[. . .]

return (
	&lt;div class=&quot;popover-hint&quot;&gt;
        &lt;article class={classes}&gt;{content}&lt;/article&gt;
        {showFolderContent &amp;&amp; (
	        &lt;div class=&quot;page-listing&quot;&gt;
	          {options.showFolderCount &amp;&amp; (
	            &lt;p&gt;
	              {i18n(cfg.locale).pages.folderContent.itemsUnderFolder({
	                count: allPagesInFolder.length,
	              })}
	            &lt;/p&gt;
	          )}
	          &lt;div&gt;
	            &lt;PageList {...listProps} /&gt;
	          &lt;/div&gt;
	        &lt;/div&gt;
        )}
	&lt;/div&gt;
)
This wraps the portion of the page that shows folder content in a conditional, which can be toggled off by adding a variable to any page‚Äôs frontmatter.

